         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translations</head>
            <div type="translation" source="#jmr-jbwp-rgg2003" xml:lang="en"><p>Greetings, fortunate Hesychios!</p></div>
            </div>
    
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>A favourable acclamation (greetings) and not a sepulcral formula (farewell). </p><p> 
               For Hesychios see <ref type="inscription" n="C.43">C.43</ref>, <ref type="inscription" n="C.65">C.65</ref>, <ref type="inscription" n="C.749">C.749</ref>, <ref type="inscription" n="C.66">C.66</ref>, <ref type="inscription" n="C.73">C.73</ref>.
               Καλόκερος (= Καλόκαιρος)  a name of good omen (see Robert, <ref target="https://zenon.dainst.org/Record/000209641">Hellenica IX</ref>, 64.f),
               is apparently being used as an epithet. Ἡσύχιος, meaning 'tranquil' indicates 
               a clearly related idea in the mind of the name-giver.</p>
         </div>
         
